		[unit]
			description=_"Blum Duk was renowned among his goblin clan for having tamed one of the Dire Wolves of the mountains, and he had the courage to match. His leadership and skills alone were what kept the areaГўв‚¬в„ўs goblins alive despite human and elvish menaces. Rumor had it that his wolf had slain fifty men and a hundred Elves.

Thus, when he heard of the awful monster that was inhabiting the area, it was only natural that he ride out alone to face it. All the other goblins expected him to slay the creature easily and drag back its carcass to feast on.

He was in for quite a shock. As soon as he saw the Basilisk, Blum Duk cowered in fright. He tried to wheel his wolf around to run away, but it wouldnГўв‚¬в„ўt move. As the creature stalked towards him, he screamed his last words: Good Gog, dog, are yer legs made of stone?!
(inscribed by Elvish Pillager)"
			name=_"Blum Duk"
			random_traits=no
			type="Direwolf Rider"
